metadata.title: Cessna 206
aws::graph::propositions: # Government Agencies Operating Cessna 206 Aircraft
Argentine Federal Police operates one P206A confiscated from drug smugglers since 1995.
The P206A operated by Argentine Federal Police remains in service as of 2020.
Argentine National Gendarmerie operates two U206 aircraft.
The two U206 aircraft were donated to Argentine National Gendarmerie by United States in 1975.
Ottawa Police Service operates one U206G aircraft.
The U206G operated by Ottawa Police Service is used as a surveillance aircraft.
National Police of Colombia operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Directorate-General of Customs and Indirect Taxes of France operates two Cessna T206 aircraft as of July 2018.
The two T206 aircraft operated by Directorate-General of Customs and Indirect Taxes of France are due for retirement.
Institut Geographique National of France operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Indonesian National Police operates Cessna 206 aircraft.
Civil Air Patrol of United States operates one 206H aircraft.
Civil Air Patrol of United States operates 25 T206H aircraft.
Civil Air Patrol of United States operates 13 U206G aircraft.
South Dakota Highway Patrol operates one T206H aircraft.
United States Marshals operates at least six T206H surveillance aircraft.
United States Marshals began operating T206H surveillance aircraft in 2001.
United States Marshals operates T206H aircraft under a front company named Early Detection Alarm Systems.
Alameda County Sheriff's Office operates a U206G surveillance aircraft.
The U206G surveillance aircraft operated by Alameda County Sheriff's Office has the registration number N5525U.

Argentine National Gendarmerie  two U206 donated by US in 1975.

Directorate-General of Customs and Indirect Taxes  operates two Cessna T206 as of July 2018, which are due for retirement.
Institut Geographique National

Indonesian National Police

Civil Air Patrol  one 206H, 25 T206H, 13 U206G
